message: Co-Chairs of the Senate Caucus to End Human Trafficking, and along with 26 of our colleagues from across the political spectrum, we have introduced the Stop Enabling Sex Traffickers Act. This narrowly crafted legislation has the support of numerous anti-human trafficking advocacy groups and law enforcement organizations around the country.

data.description: A 1996 law written to protect children now puts them in danger
data.title: How Congress Can Crack Down On Sex Trafficking
